The paper deals with the modeling and analysis of selfish behavior in network creation, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and network science (cs.NI). The analysis involves studying the performance of simple greedy algorithms, which is a common approach in algorithm design and analysis (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves empirical analysis of network creation, which could potentially fall under social networks (cs.SI).
